  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To examine pancreatic islet function and incretin function during intravenous and oral
      stimulation &gt;2 years after gastric bypass surgery in patients with normal glucose tolerance.
      We hypothesize that islet cell and incretin function is enhanced in response to oral, but not
      intravenous, stimulation - i.e. incretin released from the gut in response to oral
      stimulation play a key role for the enhanced islet function after gastric bypass surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
